      "message": "I did this because my read of the vk docs was that you *can* get everything using vkGetInstanceProcAddr. It just might go through an extra hop to get to a VkDevice-specific implementation. This constructor is publicly exposed, so I was trying to make it easy for a client that wanted to perform custom vk interface setup using a GetInstanceProc (e.g. insert vk call logging) without also having to write a GetDeviceProc. I\u0027m not that attached to it, though.",
